title: 7A-WEST
text:
Posted: October 17, 2015 at 2:04 a.m. 
FORT SMITH NORTHSIDE 30, ROGERS 9 
FORT SMITH — Quarterback Max Frazier rushed for two touchdowns and passed for another as the Fort Smith Northside (3-4, 2-2 7A-West) scored 24 consecutive points and defeated Rogers (1-6, 1-3) in a 7A-West Conference game at Mayo-Thompson Stadium. 
Rogers led 9-6 late in the first half but Northside kicked a field goal right before halftime and then opened the second half with a touchdown drive for a 16-9 lead. 
Frazier’s 69-yard touchdown pass to Brennon Lewis tied the game at 6-6 in the first quarter. He rushed for two touchdowns in the fourth quarter, including a 34-yard run that gave the Grizzlies a 30-9 lead. 
Frazier rushed 18 times for 140 yards and was 6 of 13 passing for 122 yards and 1 score. Northside finished with 233 yards rushing. 
Rogers manged just 47 yards rushing in the second half after having 142 yards on the ground in the first half. Rogers quarterback Max Horton and slot back Milacio Freeland left the game in the first half with injuries and did not return. Freeland had 64 yards on seven carries before being injured. 
FORT SMITH SOUTHSIDE 20, ROGERS HERITAGE 0 
ROGERS — Senior quarterback Cooper Johnson scored two first-half touchdowns and ran for 100 yards as the Rebels (4-3, 2-2 7A-West) took a 20-0 lead into halftime and were never threatened in the second half by Rogers (0-7, 0-4). 
Johnson scored on runs of 1 and 2 yards. Junior Kobe Rogers scored Southside’s other touchdown on a 10-yard run.
